y", "pub_date": "2024-12-09 14:30:00"}, {"id": "4742991", "title": "Wall Street Breakfast Podcast: Google Payment Counters CFPB Oversight With Lawsuit", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt='Google\"s headquarters in Silicon Valley in Mountain View, California.' data-id=\"1163973538\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"5000px\" height=\"3333px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">JHVEPhoto</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <p>Listen below or on the go on <a href=\"https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/wall-street-breakfast/id1358381502?mt=2\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/show/05uLjJxkVgQsRk8LWLCLpx?si=r3_yJgxiQiivJwNQG8WNew&amp;nd=1\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spotify</a></p> <p><div class=\"pcast hidden-print\">\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-1\">\n    <img alt=\"\" class=\"pcast__top-img pcast__marketing\" src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2018/11/21/podcast_series_header.png\">\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-2\"><iframe src=\"https://widget.spreaker.com/player?episode_id=63236653&amp;theme=light&amp;playlist=false&amp;playlist-continuous=false&amp;chapters-image=true&amp;episode_image_position=right&amp;hide-logo=true&amp;hide-likes=true&amp;hide-comments=true&amp;hide-sharing=true&amp;hide-download=true&amp;color=ff6900\" width=\"100%\" height=\"200px\" frameborder=\"0\" sap-id=\"4\"></iframe></div>\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-3\">\n    <div class=\"pcast__ad-container\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n</p> <p>Google Payment (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOG\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOG</a>) placed under <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376769-google-payment-cfpb-supervision-company-lawsuit\">CFPB supervision</a>, company hits back with lawsuit. (00:28) Apollo Global Management (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/APO\" title=\"Apollo Global Management, Inc.\">APO</a>) and Workday (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WDAY\" title=\"Workday, Inc.\">WDAY</a>) set to <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376775-apollo-global-management-and-workday-set-to-join-sp-500\">join S&amp;P 500</a>. (01:30) Omnicom (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OMC\" title=\"Omnicom Group Inc.\">OMC</a>) is said to near <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376005-omnicom-is-said-to-near-mega-merger-with-interpublic\">mega-merger</a> with Interpublic. (02:02)</p> <p>This is an abridged transcript of the podcast.</p> <p>The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau has established supervisory authority over Alphabet's (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOG#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">GOOG</a>) (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOGL#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">GOOGL</a>) Google Payment, citing \"reasonable cause\" to determine that its conduct poses risks to consumers.</p> <p>The watchdog pointed to Google's practices in investigating allegedly erroneous transactions, and its conduct in connection with the prevention of fraudulent and unauthorized transactions.</p> <p>The CFPB clarified that its <a href=\"https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-orders-federal-supervision-of-google-following-contested-designation/\" rel=\"nofollow\">order</a> \"does not constitute a finding that the entity has engaged in wrongdoing.\"</p> <p>In response, Google <a href=\"https://storage.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.dcd.275545/gov.uscourts.dcd.275545.1.0.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">sued</a> the CFPB, claiming the order would subject it to \"burdensome supervision\" and is \"in excess of statutory authority.\"</p> <p>The company claimed that the CFPB relied on \"33 cherry-picked complaints\" involving peer-to-peer payments that it discontinued earlier this year.</p> <p>The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376769-google-payment-cfpb-supervision-company-lawsuit\">CFPB said</a> it relied on 267 consumer complaints, and the regulatory framework for the designation does not specify the degree of risk needed to justify supervision.</p> <p>Apollo Global Management (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/APO#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">APO</a>) and Workday (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WDAY#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">WDAY</a>) will replace Qorvo (NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/QRVO#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">QRVO</a>) and Amentum Holdings (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMTM\" title=\"Amentum Holdings, Inc.\">AMTM</a>) in the S&amp;P 500, respectively, before the open of trading on Monday, <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376775-apollo-global-management-and-workday-set-to-join-sp-500\">December 23</a>.</p> <p>Qorvo and Amentum Holdings will replace Kelly Services Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KELYA\" title=\"Kelly Services, Inc.\">KELYA</a>) and Service Properties Trust (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SVC\" title=\"Service Properties Trust\">SVC</a>) in the S&amp;P SmallCap 600, respectively.</p> <p>S&amp;P SmallCap 600 constituents Comerica (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CMA\" title=\"Comerica Incorporated\">CMA</a>) and Carpenter Technology (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CRS\" title=\"Carpenter Technology Corporation\">CRS</a>) will replace Vishay Intertechnology (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/VSH\" title=\"Vishay Intertechnology, Inc.\">VSH</a>) and Carters (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CRI\" title=\"Carter's, Inc.\">CRI</a>) in the S&amp;P MidCap 400 respectively, and Vishay Intertechnology and Carters will replace Comerica and Carpenter Technology in the S&amp;P SmallCap 600.</p> <p>Terreno Realty (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TRNO\" title=\"Terreno Realty Corporation\">TRNO</a>) and Champion Homes (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SKY\" title=\"Champion Homes, Inc.\">SKY</a>) will replace Hudson Pacific Properties (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HPP\" title=\"Hudson Pacific Properties, Inc.\">HPP</a>) and REGENXBIO (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RGNX\" title=\"REGENXBIO Inc.\">RGNX</a>) in the S&amp;P SmallCap 600, respectively.</p> <p>Omnicom Group (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OMC#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">OMC</a>) is in advanced talks to buy longtime rival Interpublic Group (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IPG#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">IPG</a>) in a deal that would create the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376005-omnicom-is-said-to-near-mega-merger-with-interpublic\">world\u2019s biggest advertising company</a>.</p> <p>The Wall Street Journal reported Sunday, citing people familiar with the matter, that a transaction could be announced as early as this week.</p> <p>Seeking Alpha has sought comment from Omnicom (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OMC\" title=\"Omnicom Group Inc.\">OMC</a>) and Interpublic (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IPG\" title=\"The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc.\">IPG</a>), and will update this story accordingly.</p> <p>The all-stock agreement is likely to value Interpublic (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IPG\" title=\"The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc.\">IPG</a>) in a range of $13 billion to $14 billion excluding debt, the Journal reported. Interpublic\u2019s (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IPG\" title=\"The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc.\">IPG</a>) market value was about $11 billion as of Friday.</p> <p>A combined company would have net revenue of more than $20 billion a year, based on 2023 figures for each company.</p> <p>Omnicom (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OMC\" title=\"Omnicom Group Inc.\">OMC</a>) is the world\u2019s third-largest ad company by revenue, while Interpublic (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IPG\" title=\"The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc.\">IPG</a>) is the fourth-biggest. A combination would overtake WPP (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WPP#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">WPP</a>) as the industry\u2019s biggest player. WPP\u2019s net revenue last year was about $15.1 billion, the Journal reported.</p> <p>Omnicom\u2019s (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OMC\" title=\"Omnicom Group Inc.\">OMC</a>) marquee clients include Disney, Amazon, AT&amp;T and PepsiCo.</p> <p>Interpublic (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IPG\" title=\"The Interpublic Group of Companies, Inc.\">IPG</a>) clients include L\u2019Or\u00e9al, Johnson &amp; Johnson and Geico.</p> <p>More articles on Seeking Alpha:</p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376075-former-intel-ceo-asks-people-to-pray-and-fast-for-intel-employees\">Former Intel CEO asks people to pray and fast for employees</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376076-stocks-with-best-odds-of-risk-adjusted-returns-deserve-attention-goldman-sachs\">Stocks with best odds of risk-adjusted returns deserve attention: Goldman Sachs</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4372046-payment-processing-firms-track-robust-spending-on-black-friday-cyber-monday\">Payment processing firms track robust spending on Black Friday-Cyber Monday</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376147-is-the-roaring-kitty-effect-over\">Is the Roaring Kitty effect over?</a></p> <p>Catalyst watch:</p> <ul> <li><p>Raymond James TMT and Consumer Conference starts and includes Cisco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CSCO\" title=\"Cisco Systems, Inc.\">CSCO</a>), Etsy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ETSY\" title=\"Etsy, Inc.\">ETSY</a>), Shake Shack (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SHAK\" title=\"Shake Shack Inc.\">SHAK</a>) and Vivid Seats (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SEAT\" title=\"Vivid Seats Inc.\">SEAT</a>).</p></li> <li><p>Last day to start tender offer for Revance Therapeutics (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RVNC\" title=\"Revance Therapeutics, Inc.\">RVNC</a>) sale to Crown Labs, which has been extended several times.</p></li> <li><p>SmartSheet (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SMAR\" title=\"Smartsheet Inc.\">SMAR</a>) shareholders vote on sale to Blackstone and Vista Equity.</p></li> </ul> <p>Now let\u2019s take a look at the markets as of 6 am. Ahead of the opening bell today, Dow, S&amp;P and Nasdaq futures are in the red. Crude oil is up 1.2% at $68/barrel. Bitcoin is down 1% at $98,000.</p> <p>In the world markets, the FTSE 100 is up 0.2 and the DAX is down 0.1%.</p> <p>The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4376784-biggest-stock-movers-monday-smci-momo-and-more\">biggest movers</a> for the day premarket: BioAge (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BIOA\" title=\"BioAge Labs, Inc.\">BIOA</a>) is down 69% after the company announced Friday it would discontinue its Phase 2 study of the weight-loss drug azelaprag due to safety concerns.</p> <div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder\"></div><p>On today\u2019s economic calendar:</p> <ul><li><p>10:00 am Wholesale Inventories</p></li></ul>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1163973538/image_1163973538.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4742991-wall-street-breakfast-podcast-google-payment-counters-cfpb-oversight-with-lawsuit", "pub_date": "2024-12-09 14:20:53"}, {"id": "4742990", "title": "Columbia Select Mid Cap Value Fund Q3 2024 Commentary", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2158301114/image_2158301114.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Coin graph with percentage signs on top\" data-id=\"2158301114\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"987px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2158301114/image_2158301114.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2158301114/image_2158301114.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/215830111